    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-05T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-05T04:00:00-05:00" n="626"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.94/60: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-05T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >November 5, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 5—6:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>522. I am confidentially informed by a member of the Italian Embassy that
                    arrangements have been completed for signature at Rome on November 6 at 7 p.m.,
                    of the Japanese-Italian Anti-Communist Pact.<note n="14" xml:id="d626fn14">For
                        translation of text of protocol concluded by Italy, Germany, and Japan
                        November 6, 1937, see <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_159">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 159</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
